00:07:18.330 --> 00:07:22.090
And you said that you feel in
the Western tradition, literature

00:07:22.090 --> 00:07:24.540
and storytelling became
separated at some point.

00:07:24.540 --> 00:07:26.030
Can you just talk about that idea?

00:07:26.030 --> 00:07:27.330
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: Well, there's--

00:07:27.330 --> 00:07:28.630
there was a thing that
happened in the--

00:07:28.630 --> 00:07:30.220
I guess, and this is
very simplifying it.

00:07:30.220 --> 00:07:31.520
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: Yeah.

00:07:31.520 --> 00:07:32.820
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: But there
was a thing that happened

00:07:32.820 --> 00:07:36.080
around 100 years ago in
the Modernist Movement

00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:41.590
where people became so interested
