a debate internally within religion

00:15:43.870 --> 00:15:45.890
and forces of secularism or--

00:15:45.890 --> 00:15:47.470
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: I mean, yeah,
it's one of the things that happens

00:15:47.470 --> 00:15:52.280
in the book, but I think there's
something sort of under that.

00:15:52.280 --> 00:15:57.400
And the book has-- there's
a frontispiece to the book,

00:15:57.400 --> 00:16:03.680
this famous etching of Goya's
which is known as the sleep

00:16:03.680 --> 00:16:06.380
of reason brings forth monsters.

00:16:06.380 --> 00:16:12.580
But what is interesting is in
his commentary, on that picture,

00:16:12.580 --> 00:16:15.610
he said something more complicated.

00:16:15.610 --> 00:16:18.590
When you look at the picture, you
think what you are being told is

00:16:18.590 --> 00:16:22.310
that reason is good and
unreason is bad, you know?

00:16:22.310 --> 00:16:25.580 position:56%
But in his commentary, he said
something more nuanced, if you like.

00:16:25.580 --> 00:16:31.830
He says that when reason and
fantasy come together, then--

00:16:31.830 --> 00:16:34.610
I mean, to paraphrase, then they
become a great creative force

00:16:34.610 --> 00:16:37.530
and they're the parents
of the arts and so on.

00:16:37.530 --> 00:16:40.610
But when they're torn apart from
each other, it's when the kind

00:16:40.610 --> 00:16:42.680
of monstrous aspects
begin to emerge.

00:16:42.680 --> 00:16:49.580
So, I really took that as my cue to
say I want to write about a world

00:16:49.580 --> 00:16:54.270
which is not just opposing these
two forces but trying to say

00:16:54.270 --> 00:16:56.060
that when they come
together, they are creative

00:16:56.060 --> 00:16:58.770
and when they're taken
apart, they're destructive.

00:16:58.770 --> 00:17:03.620
So, you know, the novel begins with
a man of reason falling in love

00:17:03.620 --> 00:17:08.700 position:56%
with a creature of fantasy and their
union produces all these children

00:17:08.700 --> 00:17:10.360
who become the novel, if you like.

00:17:10.360 --> 00:17:14.330
So, they're-- that's sort of, in
a way, shows the creative force

00:17:14.330 --> 00:17:15.960
of the union of these things.

00:17:15.960 --> 00:17:18.980
And then there's this war
which is an illustration

00:17:18.980 --> 00:17:20.280
of the opposite, you know?

00:17:20.280 --> 00:17:22.190
So, it's trying to
say both those things.

00:17:22.190 --> 00:17:25.030
And yes, of course, one of
the ways it says it is to talk

00:17:25.030 --> 00:17:29.140 position:56%
