very strange things have

00:18:15.370 --> 00:18:16.930
started happening.

00:18:16.930 --> 00:18:21.540
And I-- in the novel it's called
"The Time of the Strangenesses".

00:18:21.540 --> 00:18:22.840
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: Right.

00:18:22.840 --> 00:18:24.470
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: And I kind--
And even though the strangenesses

00:18:24.470 --> 00:18:27.980
in the novel, a kind of
surrealist strangenesses, really,

00:18:27.980 --> 00:18:30.600
I think we live in that time.

00:18:30.600 --> 00:18:36.160
I think we live in a time in
which the rate of transformation

00:18:36.160 --> 00:18:40.210
and the radical nature of
transformation, you know, both--

00:18:40.210 --> 00:18:44.820
the world is changing both very
extremely and at very high speed.

00:18:44.820 --> 00:18:49.290
And that strangeness, that
alienation that I think many

00:18:49.290 --> 00:18:52.830
of us would consequently
feel is kind of the mood

00:18:52.830 --> 00:18:54.340
in which the book is set.

00:18:54.340 --> 00:18:56.630
