00:27:36.560 --> 00:27:37.860
Anyway--

00:27:37.860 --> 00:27:39.160 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: But do you think--

00:27:39.160 --> 00:27:40.460 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: But I think the--

00:27:40.460 --> 00:27:41.760
I mean, look, I'm a
migrant, you know?

00:27:41.760 --> 00:27:43.060
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: Yeah.

00:27:43.060 --> 00:27:44.360
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: I mean,

00:27:44.360 --> 00:27:45.910
I have spent my life
bouncing across the world.

00:27:45.910 --> 00:27:50.800
And that started off in India--
long time in England, now,

00:27:50.800 --> 00:27:53.680
almost 20 years in America.

00:27:53.680 --> 00:27:59.390
And my life is being defined by
that act of movement, you know?

00:27:59.390 --> 00:28:03.150
And I'm grateful for it and
I think it's been something

00:28:03.150 --> 00:28:07.160
which has created the kind
of artist that I have become.

00:28:07.160 --> 00:28:14.390 position:56%
And I think on the hold, it was this
age which is an age of migration,

00:28:14.390 --> 00:28:20.330 position:56%
has been very enriching both for the
communities to which migrants come

00:28:20.330 --> 00:28:24.020
and to the migrants who
come to those communities.

00:28:24.020 --> 00:28:26.830
All you have to do is walk down
the streets of any great city

00:28:26.830 --> 00:28:30.630
in the world now and you have the
stories of the whole world bumping

00:28:30.630 --> 00:28:34.940
into each other on the streets
and that's seems to me much richer

00:28:34.940 --> 00:28:40.300
than some kind of narrow
pure culture.

00:28:40.300 --> 00:28:45.580
I'm on the hold in not a great fan
of the idea of cultural purity.

00:28:45.580 --> 00:28:48.490
I think when people start
talking about cultural purity,

00:28:48.490 --> 00:28:51.500
other people start dying, you know?

00:28:51.500 --> 00:28:55.820
I mean, Hitler was somebody who
talked about cultural purity.

00:28:55.820 --> 00:29:01.600
I'm in favor of dirt, you
know, cultural impurity.

00:29:01.600 --> 00:29:05.450
Let's have a lot of just
stuff, dirt mixed in there.

00:29:05.450 --> 00:29:09.980
Then people first of all-- first
of all, people tend to stay alive

00:29:09.980 --> 00:29:11.960
