00:29:30.510 --> 00:29:31.810
Are there--

00:29:31.810 --> 00:29:33.110
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: No, no, no.

00:29:33.110 --> 00:29:34.410
No, I'm not going to say that.

00:29:34.410 --> 00:29:35.710
I mean, I--

00:29:35.710 --> 00:29:37.010
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: Yeah.

00:29:37.010 --> 00:29:38.310
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: You know, I
think if we talk about the art

00:29:38.310 --> 00:29:39.610
of the novel, I think it's
a very, very rich time

00:29:39.610 --> 00:29:41.610
in world literature for a start.

00:29:41.610 --> 00:29:44.960
I think it's a very rich time in
