novelistic about it.

00:35:26.940 --> 00:35:31.210
The length of time you
have available allows you

00:35:31.210 --> 00:35:34.210
to do what is difficult
to do in films.

00:35:34.210 --> 00:35:37.510
It allows you to have time
to develop a character,

00:35:37.510 --> 00:35:39.850
to have many different story lines.

00:35:39.850 --> 00:35:41.960
I mean, you think of something
like "Game of Thrones",

00:35:41.960 --> 00:35:45.200
there's an unbelievable
number of story lines in that.

00:35:45.200 --> 00:35:48.120
And I, you know, I wonder
how people keep them all

00:35:48.120 --> 00:35:50.930
in their heads but
it works, you know?

00:35:50.930 --> 00:35:53.430
So, there's something
novelistic about this.

00:35:53.430 --> 00:35:55.230
And, yeah, I'm interested.

00:35:55.230 --> 00:35:56.530
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: But it
isn't the novel, right?

00:35:56.530 --> 00:35:57.830
I mean you--

00:35:57.830 --> 00:35:59.130
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: I mean, no,

00:35:59.130 --> 00:36:00.430
nothing is the novel,
the novel is the novel.

00:36:00.430 --> 00:36:01.730
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: Right, right.

00:36:01.730 --> 00:36:03.030
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: You know?

00:36:03.030 --> 00:36:04.330
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: Right.

00:36:04.330 --> 00:36:05.630
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: And one of
the great things about the novel,

00:36:05.630 --> 00:36:06.930
you know, is that everything.

00:36:06.930 --> 00:36:08.480 position:56%
Almost since the birth of the novel,

00:36:08.480 --> 00:36:11.780
people have been predicting the
death of the novel, you know?

00:36:11.780 --> 00:36:14.430
And every single new thing

00:36:14.430 --> 00:36:17.630
that comes along is
supposed to kill the novel.

00:36:17.630 --> 00:36:20.990
You know, radio is supposed
to kill the novel, cinema,

00:36:20.990 --> 00:36:24.070
television, you know, the internet.

00:36:24.070 --> 00:36:26.520
Everything is supposed to kill
the novel and yet, you know,

00:36:26.520 --> 00:36:29.740
the novel obstinately
refuses to die.

00:36:29.740 --> 00:36:31.040
And I'll tell you why.

00:36:31.040 --> 00:36:34.350
It's because people like it.

00:36:34.350 --> 00:36:36.150
Things--

00:36:36.150 --> 00:36:39.670
[ Applause ]

00:36:39.670 --> 00:36:42.920
I mean, very interesting
what-- you know, the eBooks,

00:36:42.920 --> 00:36:45.430
they were supposed
to kill the novel.

00:36:45.430 --> 00:36:48.240
So, they arrived, eBooks,
and they went like a rocket,

00:36:48.240 --> 00:36:49.540
"voom", like that, you know?

00:36:49.540 --> 00:36:53.980 position:56%
And everybody-- including everybody
in the publishing industry panicked.

00:36:53.980 --> 00:36:57.950
And they got to about
17, 18% of the market

00:36:57.950 --> 00:37:01.280
and they completely plateaued.

00:37:01.280 --> 00:37:07.130
And now, they're actually dropping
whereas the sales of this dinosaur

00:37:07.130 --> 00:37:11.830
of an object, the hardcover novel,
sales are going up, you know?

00:37:11.830 --> 00:37:13.730
Our bookstores were
getting out of business,

00:37:13.730 --> 00:37:17.220
now there's little indication
that bookstores are beginning

00:37:17.220 --> 00:37:19.830 position:56%
to open rather than close, you know?

00:37:19.830 --> 00:37:21.630
So--

00:37:21.630 --> 00:37:25.550
[ Applause ]

00:37:25.550 --> 00:37:27.430
So, you know, here's this--

00:37:27.430 --> 00:37:32.630
sometimes I had to go and give
a talk at Google, you know,

00:37:32.630 --> 00:37:34.700
in Mountain View, California.

00:37:34.700 --> 00:37:37.460
And I said audience as big as this

00:37:37.460 --> 00:37:41.220
but entirely composed
of 21-year-old techies.

00:37:41.220 --> 00:37:43.430
[ Laughter ]

00:37:43.430 --> 00:37:46.290
And, I mean, very smart kids.

00:37:46.290 --> 00:37:50.830
And I said to them, you know,
this is a very remarkable piece

00:37:50.830 --> 00:37:54.850
of sophisticated hardware.

00:37:54.850 --> 00:37:56.980
I said, you know, if you--

00:37:56.980 --> 00:38:03.420
what happens if you drop
your laptop in the bath?

00:38:03.420 --> 00:38:04.720
It's screwed.

00:38:04.720 --> 00:38:10.720 position:56%
So, if you drop that in the bath,
