00:38:39.930 --> 00:38:41.420
So, this is--

00:38:41.420 --> 00:38:43.610
[ Applause ]

00:38:43.610 --> 00:38:47.170
This is actually more
sophisticated, you know?

00:38:47.170 --> 00:38:48.500
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: Fantastic.

00:38:48.500 --> 00:38:51.430
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: And also,
it doesn't become obsolete.

00:38:51.430 --> 00:38:53.300
The thing about computers,
which was supposed

00:38:53.300 --> 00:38:56.210
to be this wonderful new
thing, is they become obsolete

00:38:56.210 --> 00:38:58.230
at incredibly high speed.

00:38:58.230 --> 00:39:00.450
What's a floppy disk?

00:39:00.450 --> 00:39:05.920
You know? If you have-- If 20 years
