00:43:59.950 --> 00:44:04.960
I was teaching on and off at Emory
College in Atlanta for 10 years.

00:44:04.960 --> 00:44:06.260
I'm now at NYU.

00:44:06.260 --> 00:44:11.990
And I have literally never,
never had a student come up to me

00:44:11.990 --> 00:44:15.330
and expressed a desire
for a trigger warning

00:44:15.330 --> 00:44:17.730
or safe space or any
of these things.

00:44:17.730 --> 00:44:20.020
It's never happened.

00:44:20.020 --> 00:44:25.050
And so, I think if
it were to happen,

00:44:25.050 --> 00:44:27.480
I would have a very clear answer,

00:44:27.480 --> 00:44:32.800
which is that a university is a
place where exactly is a place

00:44:32.800 --> 00:44:36.850
where you must be exposed to ideas
you have not had before and some

00:44:36.850 --> 00:44:39.410
of which, which you might not like.

00:44:39.410 --> 00:44:41.510
That's what you are there for.

00:44:41.510 --> 00:44:47.050
[ Applause ]

00:44:47.050 --> 00:44:50.530
And that the only safe space they
can be in a university is to have--

00:44:50.530 --> 00:44:56.210
is a safe space for ideas, not a
safe space from ideas, you know?

00:44:56.210 --> 00:44:58.670
And if you can't stomach that,

00:44:58.670 --> 00:45:01.200
then maybe you shouldn't
be at a university.

00:45:01.200 --> 00:45:06.090
Maybe you should be working
at KFC or something, you know?

00:45:06.090 --> 00:45:09.760
Because, really, that's why people
go to college, they go to college

00:45:09.760 --> 00:45:12.390
to have-- to learn how to think.

00:45:12.390 --> 00:45:15.520
And you cannot learn how to think
unless you are exposed to thinking,

00:45:15.520 --> 00:45:18.760
which is not the thinking
