00:46:46.950 --> 00:46:50.620
&gt;&gt; For you, what was the hardest
aspect of storytelling to tackle,

00:46:50.620 --> 00:46:52.940
and how did you approach it?

00:46:52.940 --> 00:46:54.880
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie:
Everything is hard.

00:46:54.880 --> 00:46:57.480
I mean, it's not easy, you know?

00:46:57.480 --> 00:46:59.520
If it was easy, everybody
would do it.

00:46:59.520 --> 00:47:03.510
And that would be awful
because then--

00:47:03.510 --> 00:47:06.400
[ Laughter ]

00:47:06.400 --> 00:47:14.970
Well, look, the hardest thing
is to say something interesting

00:47:14.970 --> 00:47:20.960
and the great gamble of
writing is that you don't know

00:47:20.960 --> 00:47:25.100
if what you think is interesting
will be interesting to anyone else.

00:47:25.100 --> 00:47:28.910
You know, I mean, I remember
when I finished writing

00:47:28.910 --> 00:47:34.170
"Midnight's Children" all those
years ago, I remember thinking

00:47:34.170 --> 00:47:36.000
to myself, you know,
I think this is--

00:47:36.000 --> 00:47:38.810
I think this is a good
book, I thought.

00:47:38.810 --> 00:47:41.890
I had absolutely no--
Nobody knew who I was.

00:47:41.890 --> 00:47:45.460
I was completely unknown
as a writer.

00:47:45.460 --> 00:47:50.190
And I was completely uncertain
whether anybody would agree

00:47:50.190 --> 00:47:52.870
with my assessment of it, you know?

00:47:52.870 --> 00:47:54.170
I mean, I think it's a good book

00:47:54.170 --> 00:47:56.810
but supposing nobody
else does, then what?

00:47:56.810 --> 00:48:03.910 position:56%
And that's really the gamble of art,
you know, is that you do this thing

00:48:03.910 --> 00:48:06.770
which when you're doing it
feels like a very private act.

00:48:06.770 --> 00:48:10.340
You're sitting by yourself
in a room for five years.

00:48:10.340 --> 00:48:14.030
It took me five years
to write that book.

00:48:14.030 --> 00:48:17.060
And really, it's just you and the
book that's all there is, you know?

00:48:17.060 --> 00:48:20.050
And then at the end of it,
you send it out of the room

00:48:20.050 --> 00:48:23.470
and suddenly this private
act becomes a public act,

00:48:23.470 --> 00:48:27.110
and you have to hope that
somebody gets it, you know?

00:48:27.110 --> 00:48:29.210
And that's the-- I
think that's the gamble

00:48:29.210 --> 00:48:31.220
and you just you never
know if it's going to work.

00:48:31.220 --> 00:48:34.240
And when it works,
it's pretty damn good.

00:48:34.240 --> 00:48:37.710 position:56%
When it doesn't work, it's horrible.

00:48:37.710 --> 00:48:41.160
And I can't say more
than that, really.

00:48:41.160 --> 00:48:46.550
I mean, it's the hardest thing
I've ever tried to do writing

00:48:46.550 --> 00:48:48.070
but it's also the most rewarding.

00:48:48.070 --> 00:48:54.100
&gt;&gt; Since you brought up "Midnight's
