00:56:44.160 --> 00:56:45.460
Some of your critics say this.

00:56:45.460 --> 00:56:47.980
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: Well, first
of all, it's not required to talk

00:56:47.980 --> 00:56:50.250
about everything, you
know what I mean?

00:56:50.250 --> 00:56:52.630
Freedom of speech is
the right to speak

00:56:52.630 --> 00:56:55.500
about what you want
you to talk about.

00:56:55.500 --> 00:56:59.020
And I'm not obliged to
talk about anything.

00:56:59.020 --> 00:57:01.100
You know, I talk about the
things I want to talk about.

00:57:01.100 --> 00:57:04.160
But the point I'm trying
to make is that there is--

00:57:04.160 --> 00:57:08.930
the value of this thing
is that it is the freedom

00:57:08.930 --> 00:57:11.840
on which all other freedoms depend.

00:57:11.840 --> 00:57:13.980
If you don't have free expression,

00:57:13.980 --> 00:57:17.310
you don't actually have
a free society, you know?

00:57:17.310 --> 00:57:19.660
So, that's why it's valuable.

00:57:19.660 --> 00:57:23.870
I mean, you may-- you know, people
are completely free to disapprove

00:57:23.870 --> 00:57:25.890
of what I say or to disapprove

00:57:25.890 --> 00:57:30.040
of the things I don't talk
about, fair enough, you know?

00:57:30.040 --> 00:57:31.340
That's not the point I'm making.

00:57:31.340 --> 00:57:34.780
I don't have to make a speech on
every subject in the world in order

00:57:34.780 --> 00:57:37.250
to prove that I believe
in free speech.

00:57:37.250 --> 00:57:39.820
I talk about what I want to talk
about and let other people talk

00:57:39.820 --> 00:57:41.260
about what they want to talk about.

00:57:41.260 --> 00:57:42.610
That's the point.

00:57:42.610 --> 00:57:45.440
Does that answer your question?

00:57:45.440 --> 00:57:46.740
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:57:46.740 --> 00:57:48.040
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: OK.

