stories with bath time stories.

01:05:54.220 --> 01:06:00.850
And I would pretend to him that the
bath water contained the stories.

01:06:00.850 --> 01:06:05.270 position:56%
So, I would dip a little cup in the
bath water and pretend to take a sip

01:06:05.270 --> 01:06:08.280
and then tell him a story.

01:06:08.280 --> 01:06:10.200
So, I would-- I said, you
know, I said that, you know,

01:06:10.200 --> 01:06:12.350
the bath is full of stories.

01:06:12.350 --> 01:06:19.030 position:56%
And so, from that bath full of
stories, it became a sea of stories.

01:06:19.030 --> 01:06:22.320
And that's-- really,
it began with my son

01:06:22.320 --> 01:06:26.400
in the bath, that's how it started.

01:06:26.400 --> 01:06:30.070
Some of it comes out of
Kashmir, because, like I said,

01:06:30.070 --> 01:06:31.830
it's where my family is from.

01:06:31.830 --> 01:06:35.140 position:56%
The book is, I think, anyone who
has any knowledge of Kashmir can see

01:06:35.140 --> 01:06:37.250
that the fictional country

01:06:37.250 --> 01:06:41.660
in the story is pretty
clearly based on Kashmir.

01:06:41.660 --> 01:06:45.690
So, like that, that's all of it.

01:06:45.690 --> 01:06:46.990
Does that help?

01:06:46.990 --> 01:06:48.290
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: I--

01:06:48.290 --> 01:06:49.590
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: Yeah.

01:06:49.590 --> 01:06:50.890
&gt;&gt; Bilal Qureshi: I think we
can take one last question.

01:06:50.890 --> 01:06:53.060
I'm sorry, but we have--

01:06:53.060 --> 01:06:59.700
&gt;&gt; Hi. I read your
book, "Joseph Anton",

01:06:59.700 --> 01:07:02.430
and about that very difficult
period of time you went

01:07:02.430 --> 01:07:06.290
through when you were in hiding
and your life was being threatened

01:07:06.290 --> 01:07:08.930
and you were actually
separated from your son

01:07:08.930 --> 01:07:12.150
and your family, much of that time.

01:07:12.150 --> 01:07:20.410
And I just wondered what
strength you were able to rely

01:07:20.410 --> 01:07:24.430
on from yourself to get
through that period of time

01:07:24.430 --> 01:07:27.280
which was a long time,
like 10 years.

01:07:27.280 --> 01:07:29.250
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: More
than 10 years, yeah.

01:07:29.250 --> 01:07:34.470
Well, I mean, I-- First of
all, I was very fortunate

01:07:34.470 --> 01:07:43.990 position:56%
and that I was surrounded by
incredibly loyal friends and family.

01:07:43.990 --> 01:07:49.810
And had it not been for
their strength, you know,

01:07:49.810 --> 01:07:52.760
I would probably have had
much greater difficulty

01:07:52.760 --> 01:07:55.360
in surviving that experience.

01:07:55.360 --> 01:08:02.810
But I did fortunately have around
me this circle of very brave

01:08:02.810 --> 01:08:05.070
and very loyal people, you know?

01:08:05.070 --> 01:08:08.170
And that was a great help.

01:08:08.170 --> 01:08:11.010
And then there's a
thing, there's a thing

01:08:11.010 --> 01:08:12.820
which relates to this
book, you know?

01:08:12.820 --> 01:08:14.610
And in this book, there are--

01:08:14.610 --> 01:08:18.000
these are characters who are
supposedly the descendants

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:21.230
of the jinn and have a little
bit of the jinn magic, you know,

01:08:21.230 --> 01:08:26.530
inside them, which when the crisis
comes, when the great war comes,

01:08:26.530 --> 01:08:31.780
they discover that power within
themselves that they're able to use

01:08:31.780 --> 01:08:34.310
to resist the attack against them.

01:08:34.310 --> 01:08:39.220
And what I was trying to say
there is something that I learned

01:08:39.220 --> 01:08:43.960
in those years, which is I
think many of us, many of us,

01:08:43.960 --> 01:08:50.170
maybe all of us, have within
ourselves unsuspected strength,

01:08:50.170 --> 01:08:55.410
unsuspected reserves
of strength that we

01:08:55.410 --> 01:08:58.750
in ordinary life have
no need to call upon

01:08:58.750 --> 01:09:01.270
and we are maybe not even aware of.

01:09:01.270 --> 01:09:05.070
But in a time of crisis, whatever
that crisis may be, you know,

01:09:05.070 --> 01:09:10.390
many of us face crises in
our family, crises of health,

01:09:10.390 --> 01:09:12.470
crises all sort of things.

01:09:12.470 --> 01:09:16.910
And I think what very often happens
is that when the crisis comes,

01:09:16.910 --> 01:09:22.440
we discover in ourselves the
strength to face it, you know?

01:09:22.440 --> 01:09:26.750
And we surprise ourselves
in our ability

01:09:26.750 --> 01:09:32.270
to resist whatever it
is that's coming at us.

01:09:32.270 --> 01:09:35.860
And I certainly thought-- I
mean, if you would ask me in--

01:09:35.860 --> 01:09:40.020
at the beginning of that period,
if you would say that's going to be

01:09:40.020 --> 01:09:41.480 position:56%
like 11 years of your life and how--

01:09:41.480 --> 01:09:44.760
what sort of shape do you think
you're going to be in at the end,

01:09:44.760 --> 01:09:48.730
I would not have bet on myself
to be in great shape, you know?

01:09:48.730 --> 01:09:51.430
But I, as I say, with
the help of these--

01:09:51.430 --> 01:09:54.240
the other people, I also found--

01:09:54.240 --> 01:09:57.920
I think I found that I was more
bloody-minded than I thought I was.

01:09:57.920 --> 01:10:02.110
I'd found that I had survival
capacities which were greater

01:10:02.110 --> 01:10:04.060
than I'd believe I did, you know?

01:10:04.060 --> 01:10:07.630
And as I say, I think
that's not just me.

01:10:07.630 --> 01:10:11.400
I think that is a characteristic
we have that when the crisis comes,

01:10:11.400 --> 01:10:14.450
we find in ourselves the
resources to deal with it.

01:10:14.450 --> 01:10:17.340
And that's what I did, nothing
else that many people do.

01:10:17.340 --> 01:10:18.640
&gt;&gt; Yes, I agree.

01:10:18.640 --> 01:10:19.940
Thank you.

01:10:19.940 --> 01:10:21.740
&gt;&gt; Salman Rushdie: Thank you.

